ğŸ“¦ Containerization (Application Virtualization)
Containerization is a lighter-weight alternative to VMs, virtualizing at the application level instead of the hardware level.
â— All containers share a single host operating system and kernel.
â— Each container runs an isolated application, with its own environment and libraries.

